1
00:00:53,520 --> 00:00:58,439
♪Like a light rain sprinkling my heart♪

2
00:01:01,200 --> 00:01:02,079
So sweet.

3
00:01:04,400 --> 00:01:09,480
♪That feeling is so mysterious♪

4
00:01:39,400 --> 00:01:40,799
My dad has been posting these sweet messages

5
00:01:41,040 --> 00:01:42,719
on Red Book since February.

6
00:01:44,040 --> 00:01:45,239
I guess they've been flirting

7
00:01:45,359 --> 00:01:46,599
since then.

8
00:01:48,239 --> 00:01:49,640
My mom's Red Book account

9
00:01:50,120 --> 00:01:52,079
was just added this February.

10
00:01:57,359 --> 00:02:00,359
What does this mean?

11
00:02:00,719 --> 00:02:02,760
Hawthorn may aid digestion, but it can't dissolve feelings.

12
00:02:02,879 --> 00:02:05,719
Dried orange peel may soothe the mood, but it can't dispel loneliness.

13
00:02:05,840 --> 00:02:07,799
If you ask me about the pulse,

14
00:02:07,920 --> 00:02:09,280
blood pressure is normal,

15
00:02:10,080 --> 00:02:11,319
but missing you is abnormal.

16
00:02:13,560 --> 00:02:14,280
That's it.

17
00:02:15,759 --> 00:02:17,840
That's the cheesy poem my dad wrote for your mom.

18
00:02:21,080 --> 00:02:21,960
You didn't know about it?

19
00:02:22,520 --> 00:02:23,240
If I had known,

20
00:02:23,360 --> 00:02:25,039
I would have made it rhyme better.

21
00:02:26,080 --> 00:02:27,960
I owe your family.

22
00:02:28,599 --> 00:02:29,439
What are you talking about?

23
00:02:31,039 --> 00:02:31,719
Nothing.

24
00:02:32,719 --> 00:02:33,439
I was saying

25
00:02:34,159 --> 00:02:35,560
I didn't expect him to be so romantic.

26
00:02:35,879 --> 00:02:37,039
My mom is simple.

27
00:02:37,599 --> 00:02:38,719
They're not a good match.

28
00:02:39,280 --> 00:02:40,240
What do you mean?

29
00:02:40,439 --> 00:02:41,960
My dad is not simple.

30
00:02:43,039 --> 00:02:45,199
He can provide emotional value.

31
00:02:45,400 --> 00:02:46,479
Why didn't you inherit that?

32
00:02:47,520 --> 00:02:49,199
We broke up without clarifying things.

33
00:02:52,199 --> 00:02:54,280
Can we discuss how to handle this first?

34
00:02:55,039 --> 00:02:56,599
Stop dwelling on the breakup.

35
00:02:56,719 --> 00:02:57,680
I want to talk about it.

36
00:02:58,199 --> 00:02:59,800
I need to get this straight today.

37
00:03:01,360 --> 00:03:02,080
Give me a reason.

38
00:03:02,240 --> 00:03:03,280
Why did you break up with me?

39
00:03:19,080 --> 00:03:21,639
I think Xiaochuan is acting weird.

40
00:03:21,759 --> 00:03:23,879
He's investigating us.

41
00:03:23,919 --> 00:03:25,719
I think they're really...

42
00:03:26,520 --> 00:03:27,680
Look at their eyes.

43
00:03:28,520 --> 00:03:29,400
Something's wrong.

44
00:03:29,680 --> 00:03:30,960
Tonight is Qixi Festival.

45
00:03:31,159 --> 00:03:32,919
We have a special event.

46
00:03:33,199 --> 00:03:35,319
Please count down from five.

47
00:03:35,840 --> 00:03:36,919
The lights will go out.

48
00:03:37,080 --> 00:03:39,039
Kiss the one you love, okay?

49
00:03:39,159 --> 00:03:40,400
Yes!

50
00:03:40,479 --> 00:03:41,599
Let's get started.

51
00:03:42,159 --> 00:03:43,360
Five.

52
00:03:44,280 --> 00:03:45,360
Four.

53
00:03:46,199 --> 00:03:47,199
Three.

54
00:03:48,240 --> 00:03:49,319
Two.

55
00:03:50,039 --> 00:03:51,120
One.

56
00:04:00,120 --> 00:04:00,840
Tell me,

57
00:04:02,280 --> 00:04:04,159
do you like me?

58
00:04:24,800 --> 00:04:25,399
That day,

59
00:04:26,319 --> 00:04:27,279
I didn't get your call.

60
00:04:28,639 --> 00:04:29,279
What?

61
00:04:31,959 --> 00:04:32,879
You had a fever that time.

62
00:04:35,120 --> 00:04:35,879
I was at the base.

63
00:04:36,600 --> 00:04:37,480
The aircraft type is confidential.

64
00:04:38,000 --> 00:04:39,319
That's why I didn't answer your call.

65
00:04:40,639 --> 00:04:42,079
Why are you bringing this up now?

66
00:04:43,360 --> 00:04:44,079
I'm leaving.

67
00:04:44,759 --> 00:04:45,319
Wait.

68
00:04:50,279 --> 00:04:51,079
Xiaochuan.

69
00:04:54,399 --> 00:04:54,879
Dad.

70
00:04:55,279 --> 00:04:55,839
Mom.

71
00:04:58,279 --> 00:04:58,959
Do you two

72
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:00,600
know each other?

73
00:05:02,560 --> 00:05:03,120
No, we don't.

74
00:05:03,759 --> 00:05:04,720
No, we don't.

75
00:05:06,639 --> 00:05:07,519
What are you doing here?

76
00:05:07,959 --> 00:05:08,480
Yeah.

77
00:05:08,759 --> 00:05:09,839
Your aunt and I are...

78
00:05:10,439 --> 00:05:11,600
Counter-espionage.

79
00:05:18,439 --> 00:05:20,199
Since you've seen it,

80
00:05:22,079 --> 00:05:22,879
then

81
00:05:23,279 --> 00:05:24,279
we won't hide it anymore.

82
00:05:24,639 --> 00:05:25,720
Your aunt and I

83
00:05:26,079 --> 00:05:27,000
are in a free love.

84
00:05:27,720 --> 00:05:28,879
We respect each other.

85
00:05:30,560 --> 00:05:31,240
This year,

86
00:05:31,680 --> 00:05:33,759
we're planning to get married.

87
00:05:38,079 --> 00:05:38,759
From now on,

88
00:05:39,000 --> 00:05:40,120
we're a family.

89
00:05:41,199 --> 00:05:43,040
You two are brother and sister?

90
00:05:43,480 --> 00:05:44,639
Brother and sister?

91
00:05:48,800 --> 00:05:49,319
Yeah.

92
00:05:50,040 --> 00:05:50,720
Xiaochuan,

93
00:05:51,120 --> 00:05:52,920
Yunfei is a few months older than you.

94
00:05:53,079 --> 00:05:54,240
From now on, he's your brother.

95
00:05:54,600 --> 00:05:55,040
Come on,

96
00:05:55,360 --> 00:05:56,000
call him brother.

97
00:05:57,519 --> 00:05:58,199
Say it.

98
00:06:08,720 --> 00:06:09,439
Brother.

99
00:06:09,800 --> 00:06:10,759
I didn't hear it clearly.

100
00:06:13,920 --> 00:06:15,519
I heard it clearly, sister.

101
00:06:16,160 --> 00:06:17,199
That's right.

102
00:06:17,439 --> 00:06:19,319
You should take care of your sister from now on, okay?

103
00:06:19,519 --> 00:06:20,160
Okay, mom.

104
00:06:20,399 --> 00:06:21,480
Tomorrow is the weekend.

105
00:06:21,720 --> 00:06:22,720
Let's have a family dinner.

106
00:06:22,839 --> 00:06:23,439
I'll cook.

107
00:06:23,720 --> 00:06:24,839
Okay, come to my house.

108
00:06:25,120 --> 00:06:26,279
I'll go to buy groceries tomorrow morning.

109
00:06:26,480 --> 00:06:27,480
I'll go with you.

110
00:06:40,680 --> 00:06:41,360
Xiaochuan,

111
00:06:41,759 --> 00:06:42,720
I'll cook a few dishes.

112
00:06:42,959 --> 00:06:44,199
You and your brother wait a moment.

113
00:06:45,079 --> 00:06:46,079
Brother.

114
00:06:57,560 --> 00:06:58,480
Stomach medicine.

115
00:07:01,240 --> 00:07:02,560
You didn't eat well again.

116
00:07:35,959 --> 00:07:37,160
Who let you rummage through my things?

117
00:07:39,600 --> 00:07:41,160
I just wanted to admire

118
00:07:41,360 --> 00:07:42,959
your achievements over the past two years.

119
00:07:44,519 --> 00:07:45,360
What kind of photo?

120
00:07:46,040 --> 00:07:46,879
Why don't you let me see?

121
00:07:46,959 --> 00:07:47,560
Your girlfriend?

122
00:07:48,079 --> 00:07:49,000
She doesn't want you to see.

123
00:08:00,319 --> 00:08:01,000
He went to open the door.

124
00:08:20,439 --> 00:08:22,160
Hello, who are you?

125
00:08:23,319 --> 00:08:24,560
Who are you?

126
00:08:25,240 --> 00:08:26,360
I... I...

127
00:08:28,959 --> 00:08:29,439
Dad.

128
00:08:30,839 --> 00:08:31,279
Dad.

129
00:08:31,319 --> 00:08:32,759
Dad, why are you here?

130
00:08:33,440 --> 00:08:34,519
Is she your girlfriend?

131
00:08:35,639 --> 00:08:36,360
No, no, no.

132
00:08:36,480 --> 00:08:37,320
No, no, no.

133
00:08:37,840 --> 00:08:38,279
Dad,

134
00:08:38,639 --> 00:08:40,200
why didn't you call before coming?

135
00:08:40,919 --> 00:08:41,399
I...

136
00:08:43,639 --> 00:08:45,279
I just happened to pass by here,

137
00:08:45,519 --> 00:08:46,440
so I came to see you

138
00:08:46,600 --> 00:08:47,639
and your mom.

139
00:08:48,879 --> 00:08:49,600
Is your mom here?

140
00:09:01,960 --> 00:09:02,960
I just

141
00:09:03,360 --> 00:09:04,639
attended a forum.

142
00:09:04,840 --> 00:09:06,039
They gave me these flowers.

143
00:09:06,559 --> 00:09:07,919
They'll wilt in a few days.

144
00:09:08,279 --> 00:09:09,840
I want to put them at your mom's place.

145
00:09:10,279 --> 00:09:11,200
Is your mom home?

146
00:09:12,879 --> 00:09:13,799
No.

147
00:09:14,519 --> 00:09:15,039
Where

148
00:09:15,279 --> 00:09:16,519
is she?

149
00:09:20,519 --> 00:09:21,879
Is someone knocking?

150
00:09:24,360 --> 00:09:25,320
I ordered takeout.

151
00:09:26,440 --> 00:09:27,600
You're cooking.

152
00:09:27,720 --> 00:09:28,840
Why order takeout?

153
00:09:41,720 --> 00:09:42,159
What...

154
00:09:42,279 --> 00:09:43,320
She was fine just now.

155
00:09:43,799 --> 00:09:44,879
What's wrong?

156
00:09:48,840 --> 00:09:49,919
Gastric perforation.

157
00:09:50,960 --> 00:09:51,919
It might be a gastric perforation.

158
00:09:52,039 --> 00:09:52,639
Take him to the hospital.

159
00:09:54,000 --> 00:09:54,799
To the hospital.

160
00:09:54,879 --> 00:09:55,559
Are you okay?

161
00:09:55,840 --> 00:09:56,559
Let's go. Take him to the hospital.

162
00:09:56,559 --> 00:09:57,440
What's going on?

163
00:09:57,519 --> 00:09:58,559
Are you okay?

164
00:10:04,600 --> 00:10:05,399
This delivery guy

165
00:10:05,840 --> 00:10:07,799
threw the flowers on the ground. Unbelievable.

166
00:10:09,600 --> 00:10:11,120
You ordered flowers?

167
00:10:12,559 --> 00:10:14,759
Don't you like the sense of occasion?

168
00:10:39,240 --> 00:10:39,960
How are you feeling?

169
00:10:40,000 --> 00:10:40,799
Are you okay?

170
00:10:44,559 --> 00:10:46,440
It's not a perforated stomach this time.

171
00:10:58,240 --> 00:11:00,480
You eat irregularly

172
00:11:00,679 --> 00:11:01,720
and stay up late working.

173
00:11:02,200 --> 00:11:03,440
Can you take better care of yourself?

174
00:11:05,559 --> 00:11:06,799
Yeah, Fei.

175
00:11:07,159 --> 00:11:09,200
You should learn to take care of yourself

176
00:11:09,279 --> 00:11:10,559
since you have a traditional Chinese medicine girlfriend.

177
00:11:10,679 --> 00:11:11,240
From now on,

178
00:11:11,320 --> 00:11:13,039
let her give you a good treatment.

179
00:11:17,960 --> 00:11:20,039
I'll make you a cup of dried orange peel tea.

180
00:11:20,120 --> 00:11:20,679
It's good for your stomach.

181
00:11:20,960 --> 00:11:22,000
I'll also prescribe some medicine

182
00:11:22,080 --> 00:11:22,840
to help you recover.

183
00:11:23,639 --> 00:11:24,440
Remember to take it on time.

184
00:11:28,399 --> 00:11:29,360
Thank you.

185
00:11:36,200 --> 00:11:36,799
Fei,

186
00:11:38,200 --> 00:11:39,320
I'm not trying to lecture you,

187
00:11:39,600 --> 00:11:41,159
but I know your job,

188
00:11:41,600 --> 00:11:42,919
I know you're busy all day.

189
00:11:43,360 --> 00:11:43,879
But

190
00:11:43,960 --> 00:11:45,519
you can't neglect your health,

191
00:11:45,840 --> 00:11:47,679
or your life.

192
00:11:47,960 --> 00:11:49,039
Don't be like me,

193
00:11:49,480 --> 00:11:51,200
who was immersed in work.

194
00:11:51,320 --> 00:11:51,960
As a result,

195
00:11:52,320 --> 00:11:53,320
I ignored your mother.

196
00:11:53,480 --> 00:11:54,840
Now I'm retired.

197
00:11:55,000 --> 00:11:57,120
I feel lonely.

198
00:11:58,559 --> 00:11:59,639
I regret

199
00:11:59,799 --> 00:12:01,840
that I didn't care enough about your mother.

200
00:12:02,080 --> 00:12:02,600
So,

201
00:12:03,679 --> 00:12:05,159
I don't blame her for divorcing me.

202
00:12:05,480 --> 00:12:05,960
Really.

203
00:12:13,559 --> 00:12:14,159
Xiaofei,

204
00:12:18,000 --> 00:12:18,759
I want

205
00:12:20,320 --> 00:12:21,480
to mend our family.

206
00:12:24,799 --> 00:12:26,480
You can sound out your mom's thoughts.

207
00:12:27,519 --> 00:12:28,559
You know what I mean, right?
